properties.flavorText: This sign has been smashed to pieces.
It's strange that a bottle of acid doesn't just melt right through. It would be great to throw at enemies, or put on their sandwiches!
This pebble just reeks of evil. It's very round, not shiny, and very evil. It would also be good to throw at people.
Barney struggled as a Norkian adventurer, so he became an evil Norkian adventurer.
Tasked with guarding Necromancer's important tomes and documents.
A small haystack made entirely of evil. The individual threads of hay reek of darkness (and evil).
A small golden coin, upon which is the King of Frigri with a moustache hastily drawn on it. It must be a form of currency in these parts.
A die that appears to have no face with six engraved on it. Let's hope your life doesn't depend on rolling a 6.

A small tome, resembling Cleric's teachings book. Scratched hastily upon the cover is the word "Forbidden" but the overall contents of the book seem the same. There are occasional footnotes that read "Evil!"
Evil Norkos Bank: A name you can trust.
Caution: The floor is made of lava!
Iron Dagger Inn: No vacancy, go away.
